body_html:
Yes. However, I do not believe it is the problem with master. I am currently trying to figure out what is going wrong when I am rebuilding Tensorflow in Android. It could be that somehow Android is still using the old build despite the existence of a newer build. I will update once I figure out what went wrong.

EDIT: It seems like I got it working. It turned out for some reason tensorflow/core/ops was not included in the tensorflow/BUILD file and once I added that the error went away.

Thank you for the help!

body:
Yes. However, I do not believe it is the problem with master. I am currently trying to figure out what is going wrong when I am rebuilding Tensorflow in Android. It could be that somehow Android is still using the old build despite the existence of a newer build. I will update once I figure out what went wrong.

**EDIT:** It seems like I got it working. It turned out for some reason `tensorflow/core/ops` was not included in the `tensorflow/BUILD` file and once I added that the error went away.

Thank you for the help!
